---
description: Do not commit or push — user reviews and publishes via GitHub themselves
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git: local changes only

- Make code changes locally in the workspace.
- **Do not** run `git commit`, `git push`, or create/update pull requests unless the user explicitly asks in the current message.
- **Do not** amend, rebase, or force-push without explicit user request.
- After completing work, summarize what changed so the user can review and commit/push when ready.

The user publishes to GitHub after their own review.
